## рҹҺҜ What I want to do next

Based on a gap audit done at the end of Session 4, Session 5 work is sequenced into three phases (5a вҶ’ 5b вҶ’ 5c) before moving on to feature phases (6, 7, 8). The audit identified a number of features and bugs that are higher-impact than the original Option A/B/C/D plan suggested, particularly around teacher class management UX.

### Phase 5a вҖ” Class management polish (the big one for this session)

Three things teachers will hit on day 1 of real use, all naturally living together:

**1. Cover photo upload (teacher side).**
- Create Supabase Storage bucket `class-covers` with RLS: teacher of class can read/write their own folder; everyone can read publicly (since the URL is referenced from the class card).
- Path convention: `class-covers/<class_id>/cover.<ext>`.
- Upload UI in the class settings page (see #3). Replace existing color cover when present, but **keep color as a fallback AND tint a subtle gradient over the photo** so the class is still visually recognizable in lists, like Google Classroom.
- Rendering: `cover_photo_url` already exists on the `classes` table вҖ” wire ClassCard, RecentClassCard, and the class detail page header to use it when present.

**2. Class ordering вҖ” drag-and-drop with sensible defaults.**
- Add `display_order` integer column to `classes` (per-teacher) AND to `class_enrollments` (per-student). Both default to creation/enrollment time so the unmoved order is "by recent."
- Use `@dnd-kit/sortable` (lightweight, well-maintained). New classes get inserted at the TOP of the list (matches Google Classroom muscle memory).
- Teacher can drag any card anywhere on `/teacher/classes`. Student can drag any card on `/student/classes`. Each persists independently вҖ” teacher and student see different orderings of "the same" list (correct).
- Persist via a small server action that updates affected rows' `display_order`. Optimistic client-side reorder for snappy feel.
- **Why drag-and-drop over pinned/recent:** it's the muscle-memory teachers already have from Google Classroom; we'll need `@dnd-kit` later for module/lesson ordering anyway, so the investment amortizes.

**3. Class settings page `/teacher/classes/[id]/settings`.**
- New "implicit sixth tab" linked from a gear icon in the class detail header (NOT in the main tabs row вҖ” settings are not a content tab).
- Houses the heavy/irreversible settings: cover photo upload, archive, delete, full invite code controls (move InviteCodePanel here as the canonical location, leave a smaller copy-only widget on the Stream tab).
- Keep the lightweight `ClassFormModal` (3-dot menu вҶ’ Edit) for fast name/section/semester/color/description changes.

### Phase 5b вҖ” UX gaps that will bite teachers/students fast

**4. Archive must preserve student access.**
Current bug: `listMyEnrolledClasses` filters out archived classes with `if (!c || c.is_archived) return null`. This means once a teacher archives a class, students *lose access* to past materials and grades вҖ” wrong. Fix: surface archived classes in a separate "Past classes" section on `/student/classes`, read-only.

**5. Add unarchive + permanent-delete to archived class menu.**
Right now archive is one-way from the UI. The 3-dot menu on archived class cards should offer Unarchive and a confirmation-gated Delete permanently.

**6. Rejected join requests should be visible to the student.**
When a teacher rejects a request, the row's status flips to `'rejected'` but it silently disappears from the student's pending list. Add a small "Rejected requests" sub-section under pending on `/student/classes` showing rejected ones with the rejection date, plus a Dismiss button (which deletes the row).

**7. Student "Leave class" button.**
Currently only the teacher can remove a student. Add a Leave class button in the student class detail page (with confirmation), which deletes the student's `class_enrollments` row.

**8. "Copy invite link" button in InviteCodePanel.**
Currently the panel copies the code; teachers also need to copy the full URL. Add a second copy button alongside that copies `${origin}/join/${code}`.

### Phase 5c вҖ” Tech debt punch list (the original Session 5 plan)

These are smaller but they should be cleared before more features pile up.

**9. Topnav title bug.** `/teacher/classes/[id]` and `/student/classes/[id]` both show the route segment (UUID or invite code) in the topnav instead of the class name. Topnav lives in `src/components/dashboard/TopNavbar.tsx`. Fix likely involves a layout-level page-title context.

**10. `classes` table INSERT RLS hole.** Two policies (`classes_insert_policy`, `unified_insert_classes`) both have NULL `with_check`, meaning ANY authenticated user can insert ANY class. Replace both with a single `with_check` policy: `teacher_id = auth.uid() AND get_user_role(auth.uid()) = 'teacher'`.

**11. Folder rename.** `src/components/students/` вҶ’ `src/components/student/` (singular) for consistency with `teacher/`. Update three import sites: `JoinConfirmCard`, `StudentClassesView`, `StudentDashboardView`, plus `JoinClassModal`.

**12. Debug console.log cleanup.** Remove `console.log('[middleware]')` and `console.log('User Role detected:', role)` from `src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts` and `auth/callback/route.ts`.

**13. Orphaned profile row.** Delete `admin@arklms.edu` orphan from `profiles`.

### Phase 6 вҖ” Class Stream / Announcements (next session after Phase 5)

The smallest real LMS-content feature; builds the post-creation patterns we'll reuse for modules/activities. Replaces the empty Stream tab placeholder. New tables:
- `class_announcements` (id, class_id, author_id, body, created_at, updated_at, pinned)
- `announcement_comments` (id, announcement_id, author_id, body, created_at)

Teacher can post announcements with markdown body, optionally pin one. Students see announcements in reverse-chrono order (pinned first), can comment. Notifications come later.

**Decision needed before building:** plain text, markdown (rendered with `react-markdown`), or full WYSIWYG (TipTap)? My recommendation: markdown stored, rendered with a small renderer. Cheaper than WYSIWYG, more powerful than plain text, and will reuse for module descriptions and assignment instructions. Decide once for the whole app.

### Phase 7 вҖ” Modules / Content (medium-large)

Teacher creates modules within a class. Each module has lessons. Lessons can be: rich text (markdown), file upload (PDF/doc/image via Supabase Storage), external link, embedded video. Students view modules in order with optional completion tracking. Reuses `@dnd-kit` from Phase 5a for module/lesson ordering.

New tables: `class_modules` (id, class_id, title, description, display_order, is_published, created_at), `module_lessons` (id, module_id, title, lesson_type enum, content_markdown, file_url, link_url, video_url, display_order, created_at), `module_lesson_completions` (id, lesson_id, student_id, completed_at).

### Phase 8 вҖ” Activities / Assignments + Grades (large)

Assignment creation with due dates, submission window, point value. Student submission (text/file). Teacher grading. Grades populate the Grades tab. Ties into a future notifications system.

### Future / not yet sequenced

- Co-teachers / TAs (`class_teachers` junction with role enum)
- Class duplication (copy modules/activities into a new class as template вҖ” requires Phases 7 & 8 done first)
- Notifications system (bell icon in topnav currently has a red dot but does nothing)
- Class search/filter on `/teacher/classes` once teachers accumulate many classes
- Class roster CSV export
- Topnav class color theming (pull class accent color into topnav when on a class detail page)

## рҹ”‘ Important learned constraints (DO NOT VIOLATE)

- **Microsoft Entra OAuth does NOT populate `auth.jwt() ->> 'role'`** вҖ” never use that in RLS. Always use `public.get_user_role(auth.uid())` (SECURITY DEFINER function reading from `profiles`).
- **Don't use `FOR ALL` RLS policies** вҖ” split into per-command policies (SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE). The `FOR ALL` form short-circuits other PERMISSIVE policies on INSERT.
- **Two server-action conventions in this codebase, do NOT mix:**
  - `classes.ts` returns `ActionResult<T>` envelope вҖ” UI must check `res.ok` and access `res.data`.
  - `enrollments.ts` and `joinPreview.ts` throw on error вҖ” UI must use try/catch.
  - DO NOT "normalize" one to match the other. Match each call site to its action's existing signature.
- **`is_class_teacher(p_class_id, p_user_id)` вҖ” CLASS FIRST, USER SECOND.** Session 3 wrote three call sites with arguments swapped, all silently returning false. When writing new code that calls this function, always pass `class_id` first. The natural English reading "is `<user>` the teacher of `<class>`" is misleading вҖ” the actual signature is class-first. Verify any call site before trusting it.
- Sections and class names are free text owned by the teacher вҖ” autocomplete from the teacher's previous values (`SELECT DISTINCT section/name FROM classes WHERE teacher_id = auth.uid()`).
- All joins require teacher approval вҖ” both code-entry and link-click paths create a pending `class_join_requests` row, NOT an instant enrollment.
- Invite codes вҖ” 7-char (alphabet `abcdefghjkmnpqrstuvwxyz23456789`), 7-day default expiration, presets are 24h/7d/30d/Never, teachers can Reset and Disable.
- **Next.js 16 + Turbopack: `redirect()` from `next/navigation` STRIPS QUERY STRINGS from the Location header.** Verified with curl. Workaround: do query-string-bearing redirects in middleware using `NextResponse.redirect()` with `searchParams.set()`, not in pages with `redirect('/?foo=bar')`. Path-only redirects (no `?`) work fine in pages.
- **`(dashboard)`, `(auth)` are Next.js route groups** вҖ” they don't appear in URLs. So `src/app/(dashboard)/join/[code]/page.tsx` is served at `/join/<code>`, NOT `/dashboard/join/<code>`. Middleware path matching must use the actual URL paths.
- **The `next` param flow for OAuth round-trip:** `/join/[code]` (signed-out) вҶ’ middleware redirects to `/?next=/join/<code>` вҶ’ LandingNavbar reads `?next=` and passes to OAuth `redirectTo` as `/auth/callback?next=<encoded>` вҶ’ callback honors `next` if `safeNext()` validates it (must start with `/`, not `//`). Both navbar and callback have independent safety checks (belt-and-suspenders).
- **Validate UUID-shaped route params before hitting the database.** Postgres raises `invalid input syntax for type uuid` on non-UUID strings, which surfaces as a loud error card. Pages with `[id]` segments should regex-check before querying, and treat any DB error as "not found, redirect."

## вҡ пёҸ CRITICAL: How to give me code (UNCHANGED FROM SESSION 4)

- DO NOT run my code through Gemini, Copilot, or any other AI to "fix errors." Other AIs rewrite my code (changed import styles, wrapped actions in `{ok, data}` envelopes when they shouldn't, etc.) and break the contract between files. If something errors, paste the terminal output as text вҖ” not a screenshot, not a Gemini-edited version.
- For files longer than ~50 lines, give me code as a bash heredoc (`cat > path << 'EOF' ... EOF`) so I can paste it as one block into my terminal without markdown link mangling.
- **Heredoc gotcha learned in Session 4:** even with `'EOF'` quoting, generic-bracket TypeScript like `useState<{ kind: 'idle' }>` can have its `<` eaten on some terminal/clipboard combos. If TS errors complain about `,` or `<` near a generic, this is the culprit вҖ” open the file and check the literal bytes.
- When I report errors, run `pnpm tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | head -80` and paste the text output before fixing вҖ” don't guess from screenshots.
- **My terminal mangles `user.id`, `c.id`, `result.data`, etc. into markdown autolinks** like `[user.id](http://user.id)` when copying from rendered output. The actual files on disk are fine; it's only the rendered paste that's broken. Don't be alarmed when you see this in my pastes; verify with `sed -n` or `view` if uncertain.
- One phase at a time, with verification between phases.

